<font color="#FF0000">I MADE OUT OK</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec 16 18:05:28 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
This country was nothing but swell to me when I returned.<br><br>
After a law enforcement career in DEA was cut short by a bullet, I was able to get a medical degree in part due to the GI Bill of Rights.<br><br>
While attending UCLA I was lucky enough to meet Oliver Stone and Efrem Zimbalist III who encooraged me to write screenpalys.<br><br>
I now have sold my first play to Paramount and plan on donating 5% of my income from it to the VVMF.<br><br>
God Bless this country where people are judged by the content of their character rather than the content of their lives and skin color and service.<br><br>
Phill<br>
Author &quot;The Otis Factor&quot;
